summary: Super Mario Party Jamboree for the Nintendo Switch has received mixed reviews from critics. Some, like CGMagazine and Nintendo Life, praised the game's return to the classic board game format, calling it the best in the series. Others, such as GameSpot and Eurogamer, criticized the game's crowded boards and lack of new features. TheGamer and GodisaGeek found the game to be fun but ultimately too familiar, while Checkpoint hailed it as a great party game. MobileSyrup praised the game's overall enjoyment, while IGN simply called it some of the most fun they've had all year. Kotaku noted the contrasting positive and negative reviews, highlighting the game's divisive reception.

name: Thomas Tuchel
summary: Thomas Tuchel has been appointed as the new manager of the England men's football team. The German manager, who has previously managed Borussia Dortmund and Chelsea, will take over the role in 2025. Tuchel's appointment has been met with mixed reactions, with some questioning the decision to appoint a foreign manager and others praising his coaching credentials. The Guardian has suggested that Tuchel's intensity may be well-received by the England players, while the BBC has questioned whether it was right to overlook English coaches in favor of a quick fix. Tuchel has expressed his gratitude for the opportunity and has pledged to start learning the English national anthem. The appointment is seen as a necessary quick fix for England, who have struggled in recent years. However, it is also seen as a gamble for Tuchel, who will be under pressure to deliver success for the Three Lions.
